!import-table --CRIT_Psychic --show
!import-table-item --CRIT_Psychic --Disoriented! Roll your damage dice as normal and you control the creature’s movement on its next turn. --2 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Psychic --Confused! Roll your damage dice as normal and the creature cannot differentiate friend from foe until the end of its next turn. --3 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Psychic --Good hit! Do not roll your damage dice, instead deal the maximum result possible with those dice --2 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Psychic --Great hit! Roll twice as many damage dice as normal. --3 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Psychic --Dominated! Roll twice as many damage dice as normal and you control the creature’s action on its next turn. --2 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Psychic --Psychological fracture! Roll twice as many damage dice as normal and roll on the Insanity table. --3 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Psychic --Psychological break! Deal the maximum amount of damage from your normal damage dice then roll your damage dice and add that result. Then roll on the Insanity table. --2 --
!import-table-item --CRIT_Psychic --Madness! Deal twice the maximum result of your damage dice and roll on the Insanity table. --1 --
